data.database_description: This database is designed to manage and store comprehensive data related to motorsport racing events. It includes information about circuits where races are held, details of individual races including their dates and locations, driver profiles with personal and professional attributes, constructors representing the teams competing in races, and various performance metrics such as qualifying times, race results, pit stops, lap times, and standings for both drivers and constructors. The schema establishes relationships between these entities to provide a holistic view of racing events, allowing for analysis of competition outcomes and driver/constructor performances across different seasons.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each circuit.
Reference code or abbreviation for the circuit.
Official name of the racing circuit.
City or specific location where the circuit is situated.
Country in which the circuit is located.
Latitude coordinate of the circuit's geographical location.
Longitude coordinate of the circuit's geographical location.
Altitude at which the circuit is located, if available.
Web address providing more information about the circuit.

sample_data: 1, albert_park, Albert Park Grand Prix Circuit, Melbourne, Australia, -37.8497, 144.968, 10, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melbourne_Grand_Prix_Circuit
2, sepang, Sepang International Circuit, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, 2.76083, 101.738, , http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sepang_International_Circuit
3, bahrain, Bahrain International Circuit, Sakhir, Bahrain, 26.0325, 50.5106, 10, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bahrain_International_Circuit
enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about various racing circuits including their geographical and contact details.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each race event.
Year in which the race took place.
Sequence number of the race within a particular racing season.
Foreign key referencing the circuit where the race is held.
Official name or title of the race event.
Date on which the race was conducted.
Local time when the race started.
Web address providing more information about the specific race event.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details of individual racing events including their timing and location.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each driver.
Abbreviated reference code for the driver.
The racing number assigned to the driver.
Short code representing the driver's initials or nickname.
First name of the driver.
Last name of the driver.
Date of birth of the driver, formatted as DD/MM/YYYY.
Nationality of the driver.
URL to a webpage with more information about the driver.

sample_data: 3, rosberg, 6, ROS, Nico, Rosberg, 27/06/1985, Spanish, http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nico_Rosberg
enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores comprehensive information about individual motorsport drivers.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each status type.
Description of the status, such as Finished, Disqualified, or Accident.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores possible outcomes or conditions related to a race event.

columns.columnDescription: The specific year of the racing season; serves as the primary key.
A link to a webpage providing comprehensive details about that particular season.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores information about each motorsport racing season, including a reference URL for detailed data.

columns.columnDescription: Primary key uniquely identifying each constructor.
Reference code or abbreviation for the constructor.
Official name of the constructor team.
Country representing the constructor's origin.
Web address providing more information about the constructor.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains information about constructors including their references, names, nationalities, and URLs.

columns.columnDescription: Primary key uniquely identifying each standings entry.
Foreign key linking to the race associated with these standings.
Foreign key linking to the constructor involved in this standing.
Total points accumulated by the constructor up to this race.
Current rank position of the constructor based on total points.
Text representation of the current rank position.
Number of wins the constructor has achieved in the season.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks overall standing and performance metrics for constructors across races.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each race result entry.
Identifier linking to the specific race event in which this result occurred.
Identifier for the driver associated with this race result.
Identifier for the constructor (team) linked to this race result.
Car number of the vehicle driven in the race.
Starting grid position for the driver at the beginning of the race.
Final finishing position of the driver in numeric form.
Descriptive text version of the final finishing position, often '1st', '2nd', etc.
Ordinal number representing the driver's finish order in relation to others.
Points awarded to the driver based on their finishing position in the race.
Total number of laps completed by the driver during the race.
Total time taken by the driver to complete the race.
Race completion time in milliseconds for finer granularity of timing data.
Number representing which lap was the driver's fastest during the race.
Driver's rank position in terms of overall performance, possibly relative to other drivers or teams.
Time taken by the driver on their fastest lap during the race.
The speed achieved by the driver on their fastest lap in the race.
Identifier for the status of the result, such as finished, disqualified, or retired.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores detailed outcomes of individual races, including driver and constructor performance metrics.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each entry in driver standings.
Identifier for the race associated with these standings.
Identifier for the driver whose standings are being recorded.
Points earned by the driver in a specific race.
Numeric position of the driver at the end of the race.
Textual representation of the driver's finishing position.
Total number of wins by the driver in the current season or specified context.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores the standings of drivers in races, including points and wins.

columns.columnDescription: Primary key uniquely identifying each result entry.
Foreign key linking to the race associated with this result.
Foreign key linking to the constructor involved in this result.
Points awarded to the constructor for their performance in the race.
Status of the constructor's participation, such as 'D' for disqualified.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores results for constructors in specific races, including points and status.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each qualifying session entry.
Identifier linking the qualifying session to a specific race event.
Identifier linking the driver who participated in the qualifying session.
Identifier for the constructor (team) associated with the driver.
The car number of the vehicle used by the driver in this session.
The starting grid position achieved by the driver after qualifying.
Time recorded during the first segment (Q1) of the qualifying session.
Time recorded during the second segment (Q2) of the qualifying session.
Time recorded during the third segment (Q3) of the qualifying session, if applicable.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores data about qualifying sessions for races, including driver and constructor details.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for the race event where the pit stop occurred.
Identifier linking the pit stop to a specific driver participating in the race.
Sequence number indicating which pit stop this record represents during the race.
The lap number on which the pit stop occurred.
Timestamp or textual representation of when the pit stop took place.
Duration of the pit stop, typically expressed in a time format.
Precise duration of the pit stop measured in milliseconds.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores data related to pit stop events during races, capturing details such as timing and sequence.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier of the race, linking to the races table.
Identifier of the driver, linking to the drivers table.
The lap number for which the time is recorded.
Position of the driver at the end of the lap.
Time taken by the driver to complete the lap, formatted as HH:MM:SS.mmm.
Lap time in milliseconds for precise performance measurement.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Records lap performance data for drivers in specific races.
